 critical perspectives and practitioner analyses. The diverse case studies demonstrate the considerable knowledge, skills, commitment, courage and relationships within local communities that a critical community development approach can support and encourage. Concluding with activists’ perspectives on working with the challenges of violence, the book offers insights for both an understanding of the root causes of conflict and for bottom-up peacebuilding.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCommunity development. 0aConflict management. 0aPeace-building. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Peace.2bisacsh1 aEmmanuel, Sarala, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEversley, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEversley, John, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGormally, Sinéad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGormally, Sinéad, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGowthaman, P.B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalliru, Samir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKelly, Leanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKilmurray, Avila, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKilmurray, Avila, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMalanquini, Lidiane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Prey, Monina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeppl, Renata, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRisal, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchofield, Juliet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators